args: Phew. I think that covers everything\naround this part of the beach.
You've been a most thorough guide.\nThank you, Setta.
Aw, no problem. You've treated me to an\nentire smörgåsbord of snacks by this point.\nAnd eaten twice that yourself, too.
He's got a beast of a sweet tooth, this one.\nHe's been on cloud nine getting to try new\ntreats down here.
And all of them have been scrumptious!\nThough the greatest treat of all has been\nrelishing in this peaceful atmosphere.
There wasn't so much as a hint of strife the\nwhole time we were eating. Is the beach\nentirely free of fiends?
Nah, there's some here and there. But the\ntown watch and lifeguards keep everything\nnice 'n orderly.
They keep watch to make sure no one\ndrowns. They also handle pesky fiends.

Ah, so that's what you call your marine
watchmen! Having them train for combat
and work in tandem with the land watch
is brilliantly efficient.

Right? Because of them, fiends only make
it all the way to the beach once every few
years, if that. That way, you can let loose
without having to watch your back!
Sure, if never getting to blow off steam\non fiends is your idea of ＂fun.＂ Me, I like\nthe occasional—
Nrgh! This one's tough! I can't hold it back!
A large fiend has broken through the\ndefensive line! It's headed this way.\nSetta, get to safety!
But... How? Fiends almost never show up\nat the—
You'll taste the Wyrmgrace Blade before\nyou touch the boy!
Rgh, the flames are too powerful...\nMy sword can't reach its core. Marishiten!
On it! We'll see how long those flames last\nwhen I chuck it into the sea! NRAAAH!
There. Now, let's hope that cools it off a—
Ah... It got up. It's leaving!
Tch. Guess I held back a little too much.\nI was trying to finish the job.
Perhaps, but you did buy us time.\nSetta, are you all right?
You're AWESOME, Ieyasu! What was that\nsword move just now?! You were like...\nKAPWIIING! I couldn't even SEE it!
To be honest, I thought you were\nkinda clueless, but I was WAY wrong.\nYou're a total freakin' sword master!
Ha...ha ha. You are most gracious.
But we must remain vigilant. That fiend\nmay well return to the beach before long.
We won't stop it for good unless we can\nneutralize its defensive flames somehow.\nThe question is how.
True. Hmmm, fire... How to put out a fire...
...Ah! I think I've got an idea!\nIeyasu, mind lending me a hand?
With your skills, this'll go off without a\nhitch.
Okay. The fiend's back! We'll do it just like\nwe planned, Ieyasu. Push it back towards\nthat island!
Understood. My Wyrmgrace Blade is ready!
Good, it took the bait. Now, PULL! And stay\nbehind me if you don't wanna get hurt, kid.
Got it. More to the right, Ieyasu! Right!
NOW! Fling it close to the island!
Leave it to me!\nTake this: Sakura Flurry!
...Huh. That thing went under in a hurry.\nNo sign of it coming back up, either.

Because the rip tide got that sucker. It's so
intense around that island that the whole
area is off limits. They say even the best
swimmers get pulled under.
A big, strong shell and a bunch of fire\nain't jack against a current that strong.
Interesting. And you figured Ieyasu'd\nbe strong enough to chase it there.\nNot bad, kid!
Heh. It's no biggie. Just goes to show that\neven fiends can't beat the ocean. At least\nnow we don't have to worry about—
N-no WAY! It's still... It's still alive!\nWaaaaaugh!
That was too close for my comfort.\nCan you stand, Setta?
Y-you seriously beat that thing?!\nYou really ARE amazing!
The fierce currents had stripped it of the\nflame that protected it. At that point, even\nmy humble blade was enough to lay it low.
It is all thanks to your strategy, Setta.\nThis is not my victory, but a triumph\nof local wisdom.
Oh. I...hadn't thought of it that way.
In the end, native expertise wins out.\nThis has served as a good reminder.
When I return home, I shall make a point\nof enlisting residents of the shoreline to\ndirect the efforts to protect those areas.
Sounds like a plan to me. They'll know\nshortcuts and hazards better than anyone.
That is precisely my hope. Setta, thank\nyou for your contributions to my surveying\nefforts here.
You have been a most excellent guide.\nI hope you'll consider continuing to aid\nme from tomorrow on as well.
You bet! Leave it to me, Ieyasu.\nI'll show you around all SORTS of places!
